Class Parsers

java.lang.Object
Parsers
public class Parsers extends Object
Custom JSON Parsers that read through my created JSON Files to extract the data from them and turn them into their correspondent objects. This is done through a series of streams, which ultimately turn into lists of values for each column of the table (or it can also include values for intermediate tables)

  • Method Details

    • actorParser

      public Actors[] actorParser(File actorFile) throws IOException, JSONSchemaException
      This custom parser checks for a specific set of key-value pairs that match the different columns that are in the Actors table.
      Parameters:
      actorFile - the passed file. Ideally it is the custom Actors JSON File, but it handles it if otherwise
      Returns:
      returns an array of Actors objects with their values already assigned
      Throws:
      IOException - if for some reason, the file cannot be read
      JSONSchemaException - if the passed file does not meet the valid schema

    • defaultDoubleParser

      public List<Double> defaultDoubleParser(BufferedReader reader, String key)
      This custom parser checks for a specific set of key when the value is supposed to be a double
      Parameters:
      key - the specific key that the data is going to be parsed from
      reader - the passed reader. It is assigned to the file contained in the JSON Document Parser
      Returns:
      returns a List of doubles retrieved from a specific key

    • defaultIDParser

      public List<String> defaultIDParser(BufferedReader reader, String key)
      This custom parser checks for a specific set of key when the value is supposed to be an ID for an entry in the table
      Parameters:
      key - the specific key that the data is going to be parsed from
      reader - the passed reader. It is assigned to the file contained in the JSON Document Parser
      Returns:
      returns a List of strings which contain several IDs. This is later going to be split depending on the separation character used in the JSON
